In this article, Prime Minister Netanyahu of Israel welcomes Vice President Pence and his wife Karen to Jerusalem. Netanyahu expresses gratitude for President Trump's decision to recognize Jerusalem as the capital of Israel and commends Pence for his support. The two leaders also discuss the common challenges posed by Iran and express their belief that the Iranian regime will eventually fall. They also discuss opportunities for advancing peace in the region, particularly with the Palestinians. Netanyahu emphasizes the importance of recognizing the historical connection between the Jewish people and the land of Israel. Pence thanks Netanyahu for his commitment to the US-Israel alliance and affirms the strong bond between the two countries. He also mentions his meetings with leaders in Egypt and Jordan and their shared concerns about Iran. Pence concludes by expressing confidence in the future of the US-Israel relationship under President Trump's leadership.